<h2>What it is</h2>
<p>
  CyberSim is a web-based facilitation app for fast-paced, interactive cybersecurity
  tabletop exercises. In each scenario, players work toward a familiar real-world goal — winning a close campaign,
  promoting policy change, monitoring an election — while cybersecurity threats keep getting in the way.
  The app is digital, but the exercise is best played in person, with CyberSim helping the facilitator run the game.
</p>
<p>
  The novelty of CyberSim is that, just like in life, most folks aren't focused on cybersecurity.
  They're trying to go about their business, but if they don't plan for and respond to the 
  digital dangers out there, they may hit some surprising setbacks that prevent them from reaching their goals. 
  The game teaches by making the consequences feel real, in a fictional environment where it's safe to lose.
</p>
<p>
  The core insight: most cybersecurity training describes threats. CyberSim makes you
  experience the tradeoffs – time pressure, never enough money, competing priorities – in a scenario
  that mirrors how different types of organizations actually work. Four scenarios are currently available:
</p>
<h3>Political party / election campaign (the O.G. scenario)</h3>
<p>
  Players take on a range of roles in a political party fighting an uphill election campaign — managing
  rallies, advertising, fundraising, and voter communication. Cybersecurity incidents keep
  interrupting. A volunteer rage-quits; if you don't rotate his credentials in time,
  you've got a data breach. Skip two-factor authentication for your candidate to save
  money; eventually, there's a password compromise.
</p>
