<h2>Get involved</h2>
<p>
  The most valuable contribution anyone can make is a new scenario. Scenarios are built
  in Airtable — no coding required, but you do need to think carefully about how threats
  and consequences chain together. 
  If you're part of a community or organization type that isn't represented by our current scenarios,
  and you'd like to help us build one to serve that community, get in touch and we'll walk you through it.
</p>
<p>
  If you have thoughts for how to improve any of the existing scenarios – new threats, fun plot twists, gaps you've noticed –
  let us know and we'll work to incorporate your ideas.
</p>
<p>
  Code, documentation, issue reports, and deployment feedback are also welcome. Open an
  issue on
  <a href="https://github.com/cocitizen/cybersim-UI/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
  or write to <a href="mailto:contact@cocitizen.com">contact@cocitizen.com</a>.
</p>
<p>
  If you're looking to run CyberSim for your organization and have questions, feel free to reach out.
  If you need more in-depth assistance, individual
  contributors may be available for training, facilitation, or deployment support.
</p>
